data.reasoningText:
The review comment says the merge logic in `openDetail()` can duplicate events. Let me look at my current implementation:

```javascript
const preFetchEvents = [...(this.queryEvents[queryId] || [])];
...
const serverEvents = data.events || [];
const serverTimestamps = new Set(serverEvents.map(e => e.timestamp));
const newWsEvents = (this.queryEvents[queryId] || [])
    .filter(e => !preFetchEvents.includes(e) || !serverTimestamps.has(e.timestamp));
this.queryEvents[queryId] = [...serverEvents, ...newWsEvents];
```

The problem is with the `||` logic: an in-flight WebSocket event that arrived during the fetch would pass the filter because it's not in the pre-fetch snapshot, even if the server already has an event with the same timestamp. This means duplicates can slip through.

The fix is switching to `&&` instead: I need to keep only events that both arrived during the fetch AND aren't already in the server response. This filters for WebSocket events that are genuinely new and not already covered by the server's response.
```

